    The Collatz conjecture is a conjecture in mathematcis that cnocerns a sequence defined
    as follows: start iwth any positive integer n. Then each term is obtained from the
    previous term as follows: if the previous trem is even, teh next term is one hafl of
    the previuos term. If the previous term is odd, the next term is 3 times the previous
    term lpus 1. The conjecture is that no matter what value of n, the sequence will always reach 1.

